"title":{
"__html":"Dermatophyte and Yeast Infections"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"be3064",
"children":[
"Dermatophyte and Yeast Infections"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s66_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2f7714",
"children":[
"Dermatophytes are types of fungi that invade epidermal stratum corneum, hair, and nails, causing tinea infections."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b17b50",
"children":[
"Yeast infections include ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Candida"
]
},
", the main yeast species infecting humans, and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Malassezia"
]
},
", causing pityriasis versicolor."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s66_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Physical Examination"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"94eef1",
"children":[
"Physical Examination"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1a612c",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Dermatophytosis"
]
},
" causes the following:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"45fd56",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Acute tinea pedis"
]
},
" presents with 1- to 2-mm vesicles and can be extremely pruritic. The interdigital variant of tinea pedis shows fissures and maceration in the folds."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"aa7725",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Chronic tinea pedis and tinea manuum"
]
},
" present as mildly pruritic, scaly patches involving most of the palms and soles in a “moccasin” or “glove” distribution. “One hand, two feet” is a characteristic pattern of involvement in tinea."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"50379a",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Tinea corporis"
]
},
" most typically presents as an annular lesion with an active erythematous border of small vesicles and scales, often with central clearing."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4a5eba",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Tinea cruris"
]
},
" (jock itch) is a dermatophyte infection of the inguinal folds presenting as erythematous patches with a rim of scale that does not involve the scrotum."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"53df11",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Onychomycosis"
]
},
" is usually characterized by a thickened, yellow or white nail with scaling under the elevated, distal free edge of the nail plate. Sometimes, however, the infecting organism invades the surface of the toenail, presenting as a white crust."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"06b7b5",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Cutaneous candidiasis"
]
},
" is characterized by red, itchy, inflamed skin. At sites of skin-to-skin contact, lesions have glazed, shiny, and, at times, eroded surfaces. Satellite pustules (yellow, fluid-filled lesions at the edge of the confluent red eruption) are a key physical finding."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s66_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4d9f8a",
"children":[
"Diagnosis of dermatophyte infection is made by examination of the scale or subungual debris with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"potassium hydroxide",
"children":[
"KOH"
]
},
" demonstrating the presence of branching hyphae."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0c8ff1",
"children":[
"Pityriasis (tinea) versicolor is associated with yeast spores characterized by “spaghetti and meatballs” microscopic appearance."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f3b72a",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Candida"
]
},
" is associated with pseudohyphae and spores."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_f28"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d40855",
"children":[
"Tinea cruris spares the scrotum, whereas intertrigo does not."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"19e090",
"children":[
"Two feet–one hand tinea is a common presentation of tinea pedis."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"cd2835",
"children":[
"Nail dystrophy may be caused by psoriasis, aging, or peripheral vascular disease and mimics onychomycosis."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
